FIX SUMMARY: DUBAI PREMIUM UI REFACTOR
====================================

PURPOSE
Professionalize the AccoPlacers UI to "Dubai Premium" standards by implementing structural depth, architectural consistency, and conversion-optimized UX.

KEY ARCHITECTURAL CHANGES
1. DESIGN SYSTEM (ds.css)
   Initialized a centralized design system to replace fragmented inline styles. Standardized borders from 1.5px to 1px for a cleaner aesthetic. Implemented Z-axis elevation using a tiered shadow system and hover-lift effects. Added backdrop-blur utilities (glassmorphism).

2. STYLE PURGE
   Eradicated extensive inline style attributes across core templates. Refactored index, registration, login, and dashboard templates to use semantic classes.

3. BRANDING AND LOGO INTEGRITY
   Unified logo assets across all browsers using high-resolution icons. Resolved logo mismatch issues where different pages used inconsistent assets. Clarified branding panels to eliminate UI duplication.

4. SYNTAX INTEGRITY PASS
   Performed a final surgical audit of the design system to resolve at-rule/selector errors and ensure 100% CSS compliance.

UX IMPROVEMENTS
1. REGISTRATION TRANSPARENCY
   Updated call-to-action buttons to "Accept Terms & Pay Deposit". Explicitly surfaces the deposit requirement earlier to increase high-intent conversion.

2. SECURITY VISUALS
   Injected security lock icons into sensitive document upload fields to communicate trust and confidentiality.

3. MICRO-INTERACTIONS
   Standardized all animation timings to 0.2s ease-in-out, providing a high-performance, snappy experience.

4. PRODUCTION HARDENING (Batches 007-011)
   - **Financial Integrity**: Signature-verified Stripe webhooks and double-payment prevention.
   - **Bot Defense**: Silent `fax_number` honeypots on registration and IP-based rate limiting (5 req/min) on auth portals.
   - **Administrative Intelligence**: Custom analytics dashboard for staff tracking growth and engagement.
   - **SEO/AI Discovery**: Industry-standard `llms.txt`, dynamic `sitemap.xml`, and optimized meta descriptions.

TECHNICAL DEBT REDUCTION
Converted layout-blocking inline styles to external stylesheets. Standardized CSS variable usage across all views. Improved template readability by separating logic from presentation. Implemented robust error handling for external API integrations (Stripe, OpenAI).

